Edited: 2021/11/01 23:05

Variable Unsigned Integer

Can define values from 0 up to (2^128)-1
It can also define null value
Must be written in Big-Endian format

1.- First byte
      Can define values from 0 up to 250
      Special Values;
        255:= null
        254:= value defined in the next 2 bytes   ( UINT16)
        253:= value defined in the next 4 bytes   ( UINT32)
        252:= value defined in the next 8 bytes   ( UINT64)
        251:= value defined in the next 16 bytes  (UINT128)
        
Recomendations;
  When retreiving/storing the value, the parameter type could be
    the maximum integer size parameter (i.e; Uint64)
